This paper discusses the challenges and limitations of verifying and validating agentic behavior, which is a key concern in the development of general artificial intelligence. The paper touches upon topics such as formalism, manual proof, automated behavioral governance, physical outcomes, and layered architectures. These topics are all relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the most relevant ones are likely to be cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
